April 27, 2011

C@N[7]

The 7th Princeton ACM Code@Night was on 4/15. Prefrosh came!

We provided food, liquids, caffeine, snacks, chairs, tables, heating, bathrooms, air, doors, couches, and outlets.

This episode of C@N had a theme of:
NETWORK SECURITY!

At 11 pm, Hao Lian presented his talk on Dan Kaminsky's 2008 DNS cache poisoning attack.

Sponsored by USG. Who likes us. And gave us money. To get you food. So you can code. And be happy.

C@N[5]

Come code with us all night at the 6th EVER Princeton ACM Code@Night!

We provide food, liquids, caffeine, snacks, chairs, tables, heating, bathrooms, air, doors, couches, and outlets.

This episode of C@N will have a theme of:
UNIX AND SCRIPTING!

Whether you're an expert script/unix-ist or have never heard of those things before, come to this C@N to learn more and share what you know!

Sponsored by USG. Who likes us. And gave us money. To get you food. So you can code. And be happy.
